decision_details:
- Competitive bids have been invited for the selection of contractors for 8 construction projects of the following  6 universities. Accordingly, the proposal made by Hon. Lakshman Kiriella, the Minister of Higher Education and Highways, to award the contracts as recommended by the Technical Evaluation Committees which evaluated the bids and the Standing Cabinet Appointed Procurement Committee, was approved by the Cabinet. 

*	Construction of a building for the Bio Systems Technology studies and a building for the English Language Learning Centre at the Eastern University of Sri Lanka; 

*	Construction of a housing complex for the staff of the Sabaragamuwa University of Sri Lanka; 

*	Construction of a building complex for the Department of Technological Studies at the Faculty of Applied Sciences of the South Eastern University of Sri Lanka; 

*	Extension of the West Wing building of the faculty of Management and Finance at the University of Colombo; 

*	Extension of the main library and construction of a building for the Faculty of Engineering at the University of Peradeniya; 

*	Construction of a building for the Faculty of Medicine at the Wayamba University.
